8Uu6mZPViVM.title: Danny Padilla - "Isn't Me" Official Lyric Video
8Uu6mZPViVM.description:
"Isn't Me" OUT NOW
Spotify: Spotify: https://bit.ly/IsntMeSP
Apple Music/iTunes: https://bit.ly/IsntMeAM

I met Ms. Bekah Purifoy on TV. Obviously a weird place to try and find love, but I couldn’t help but remain optimistic. I was immediately drawn to Bekah, as she was the only one who was as loud and “out there” as I was the first few days. Strong conversations and intimate questions right away, which I love. It wasn’t until after the show that I gave myself permission to REALLY consider the concept of “us”. It felt good. My friends loved her. I felt like I would’ve been letting them down by not making it work. It didn’t work. There wasn’t a scenario in which the two of us fit into each other’s lives in the way we had hoped, even though the show really pushed us to want a “love story” so badly. I went into a phase of mourning, where I couldn’t help but have consistent dreams about making different choices that could’ve resulted in us actually being together. “If I could kiss her ‘til it made more sense, God knows I’d do it all again.” I know it was an unhealthy mindset, but in that moment, I couldn’t really move on. All I could do was write about it, and so I did. “Isn’t Me” is not a bitter song, just one based in the reality I faced at the time. Coming to terms with the fact that “the last one she’ll ever love isn’t me.”

FOLLOW ME
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/dannyjpadilla
Twitter: @DannyPadilla
Instagram: @DannyJPadilla
TikTok: @dannypadilla

LYRICS

She’s who my mom had in mind for me
That unforgettable kind all the millions of eyes could see
First smile in a while that everyone believed
But permanently inside her head remained a high we couldn’t keep

Go on and tell all my friends I failed again
I couldn’t build her a world worth living in

If I could kiss her til it made more sense 
God knows I’d do it all again
Wish I could hold her til we’re more than friends 
I wanna die a happy man
Oooh
Oooh
Sorry for my eyes, but it’s hard to fight when the last one she’ll ever love
Isn’t me

She hopes I’m holding someone new today
Call me crazy, selfish but I just can’t do the same
So in love with her sister’s kids, but do they know my name?
I got too used to me believing I’d be part of their lives some day

Go on and tell all my friends I failed again
I couldn’t build her a world worth living in

If I could kiss her til it made more sense 
God knows I’d do it all again
Wish I could hold her til we’re more than friends 
I wanna die a happy man
Oooh
Oooh
Sorry for my eyes, but it’s hard to fight when the last one she’ll ever love
Isn’t me
Isn’t Me

Script Not Found is a group of amazingly talented and fun improvisers who I've grown to know super personally from going to school with them, and now we're finally taking the show to the YouTube platform! Here's the 28th episode featuring the wonderful Morgan Harvill! Be on the lookout for new episodes, and also make sure to go subscribe to the SNF YouTube page for individual games videos and exclusive content! Also, making this show is a huge team effort during every part of the production process, and if you'd like to help support us in any way and receive awesome perks in return, fund us on Patreon!
https://www.patreon.com/ScriptNotFound

Apologies! We experienced an editing glitch, where the program randomly chops off the ends of text, so "Sasha" turned into "Sa" in the intro. But don't worry, Sa isn't mad!

Script Not Found is a group of amazingly talented and fun improvisers who I've grown to know super personally from going to school with them, and now we're finally taking the show to the YouTube platform! Here's the 25th episode featuring the wonderful Eric Millegan from Bones! Be on the lookout for new episodes, and also make sure to go subscribe to the SNF YouTube page for individual games videos and exclusive content! Also, making this show is a huge team effort during every part of the production process, and if you'd like to help support us in any way and receive awesome perks in return, fund us on Patreon!
https://www.patreon.com/ScriptNotFound

Filmed by: Danny Padilla & Jordan Ebright
Wedding Footage by JL Films: http://bit.ly/JoeLanthier

"VIP" - Danny Padilla
Written by: Danny Padilla
Produced by: Danny Padilla & Cazz Brindis
Performed by: Danny Padilla

LYRICS

This is honest, babe 
And this is true
I got an independent body but I own a dependent soul too
And in this crazy, stupid attitude I somehow stumbled into you
I kinda need this moment, I do

Thank God you showed up when you did, ‘cause I was beginning to
Believe that my mean ex-girl with the stone cold heart's a perfect 10
You came from Eden and deleted my old head and now I’m saved
And I gotta say

I’m feeling pretty VIP
Gotta thank you for finding me
‘Cause you’re turning what I want into needs, yeah
Only face I see, yeah
Is a pretty little VIP

Love don’t need no gated fence or a shiny Benz when it’s homegrown as hell
And when all of my friends wanna know how it ends, I don’t kiss you and tell,
How I’m never gonna change my profile back to a photo by myself,
And damn, now I need this moment, I do.

Thank God you showed up when you did, ‘cause I was beginning to
Believe that my mean ex-girl with the eyebrow scar's a perfect 10
You came from Eden and deleted my old head and now I’m saved
And I gotta say

I’m feeling pretty VIP
Gotta thank you for finding me
‘Cause you’re turning what I want into needs, yeah
Only face I see here
Is a pretty little VIP

I’m feeling pretty VIP
I gotta thank you for finding me
‘Cause you’re turning what I want into needs, yeah
Only face I see here
Is a pretty little VIP
